rComments: Great prof  Annoyingly smart. Has thoughtful answers for nearly every question. Very tough course but worth the work.
Smart guy but tough. Good course if you want to learn about politics and inequality.
I just saw my grade. It isn't as good as I hoped but that doesn't change how I see the course. Andersen gives a great course. Same goes for soc296. Best Prof I've had.
Excellent course. Very tough and challenging but probably the most informative course I've taken. Great professor.

Bob is a very good professor and nice person, very down to earth. His tests are tricky, and he demands a lot from students. But his courses give you very different experience that you won't find in other undergrad soc courses, and to some extent are an excellent preparation for high-level studies. Worth taking it!

Interesting prof, but extremely harsh grading and terribly overwhelming workload.  Take this course if you are interested in political sociology, you will learn a lot.  But make sure prepare yourself for the greatest challenge you'll ever face in undergrad.  You've been warned
